---
permalink: /index.html
---
<div class="[ container stack-lg ][][]">
	<header class="[ stack ][][ header ]">
		<div class="[ stack-sm ][ inset ][]">
			<p class="[][][ header__category ]">A bookmarklet</p>
			<h1 class="[][][ header__title ]">{{ metadata.site.title }}</h1>
			<p class="[][][ header__heading ]">Check your progress in the <span class="[][ nowrap ][]">New York Times</span> <a href="https://nytimes.com/puzzles/spelling-bee" class="[][ nowrap ][]">Spelling Bee</a> without leaving the puzzle.</p>
		</div>

		<figure class="[ stack-sm ][][]">
			<picture>
				<source
					srcset="/images/desktop@2x.avif"
					media="(orientation:landscape)"
					type="image/avif"
				/>
				<source
					srcset="/images/desktop@2x.jpg"
					media="(orientation:landscape)"
					type="image/jpeg"
				/>
				<source
					srcset="/images/desktop@2x.webp"
					media="(orientation:landscape)"
					type="image/webp"
				/>

				<source
					srcset="/images/mobile@2x.avif"
					media="(orientation:portrait)"
					type="image/avif"
				/>
				<source
					srcset="/images/mobile@2x.webp"
					media="(orientation:portrait)"
					type="image/webp"
				/>
				<source
					srcset="/images/mobile@2x.jpg"
					media="(orientation:portrait)"
					type="image/jpeg"
				/>

				<img
					alt="Spelling Bee puzzle with Spell Check visible."
					src="/images/desktop@2x.jpg"
				/>
			</picture>

			<figcaption
				class="[][ font-sans font-sm inset ][ header__caption ]"
			>The {{ metadata.site.title }} grid shows the number of words remaining for the day’s puzzle.</figcaption>
		</figure>
	</header>

	<aside class="[ stack-xs ][][ reminder ]">
		<h2 class="[][][ reminder__heading ]">Please Note</h2>
		<p><span class="[][ nowrap ][]">{{ metadata.site.title }}</span> is made and maintained by <a href="https://ashur.cab/rera">Ashur Cabrera</a>, and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the New York Times.</p>
	</aside>

	<main class="[ stack-lg ][][]">
		<section
			class="[ stack-sm ][ inset ][ section ]"
			id="usage"
		>
			<h2 class="[][][ section__heading ]">How it works</h2>
			<p>Once you have the {{ metadata.site.title }} bookmarklet <a href="#install">installed</a>, open the <a href="https://nytimes.com/puzzles/spelling-bee">Spelling Bee</a> in your web browser and start playing like normal.</p>
			<p>Whenever you need a nudge in the right direction or just want to check your progress, click or tap the {{ metadata.site.title }} bookmarklet.</p>
			<p>Sourced from the grid of daily totals at the <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/spotlight/spelling-bee-forum">Spelling Bee Forum</a>, the {{ metadata.site.title }} grid reveals an ever-decreasing number of words remaining.</p>
			<p>Found every 5-letter word that starts with “<strong>T</strong>”? A celebratory green checkmark shows when there are no words left to uncover.</p>
		</section>

		<section
			class="[ stack ][ inset ][ section ]"
			id="install"
		>
			<header class="[ stack-xs ][][]">
				<h2 class="[][][ section__heading ]">Installation</h2>
				<p>Bookmarklet installation is a little different depending on which browser and platform you’re using.</p>
			</header>
		</section>
	</main>

	<footer class="[ stack-sm ][][ footer ]">
		<h2 class="[][][ footer__heading ]">{{ metadata.site.title }}</h2>
		<ul class="[ stack-sm ][][ footer__links ]">
			<li><a class="[][ no-underline ][]" href="https://github.com/ashur/spellcheck">View source</a></li>
			<li><a class="[][ no-underline ][]" href="https://twitter.com/ashur">Report an issue</a></li>
		</ul>
	</footer>
</div>
